CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "The Gang's All Here! - Several died-in-the-wool picnickers can be identified in this shot at the Alpha Phi Alpha picnic at North Park last Friday. They are Oscar James, Sonnyman Jackson, Dr. Ira Cornelius, Cecil Bratton and Howard Hairston.  Doc Cornelius wants all to know the tin cup holds nothing but water."
TitMainTitle: Women and men, including Rufus "Sonnyman" Jackson, Dr. Ira Cornelius holding cup, Cecil Bratton, and Howard Hairston, gathered for Alpha Phi Alpha picnic, North Park
